  "prompt": "I am planning a 4 day Holiday in North India. Where can I go?",
  "response": "Okay, a 4-day holiday in North India offers a lot of options, but to give you the BEST recommendation, I need a little more information about your preferences:\n\n**1. What kind of experience are you looking for?**\n\n*   **Mountains & Nature:**  Do you want stunning Himalayan views, trekking opportunities, and serene landscapes?\n*   **History & Culture:** Are you interested in forts, palaces, temples, and exploring historical sites?\n*   **Relaxation & Spirituality:**  Are you looking for a peaceful and rejuvenating experience, perhaps with yoga or meditation?\n*   **Adventure:**  Do you want to try things like rafting, paragliding, or jeep safaris?\n*   **Food:** Are you wanting to try lots of different cuisines?\n*   **Shopping:** Are you wanting to pick up some local goods from the area?\n\n**2. What is your budget?**\n\n*   **Budget-friendly:** Are you looking for affordable options, hostels, and local transportation?\n*   **Mid-range:** Are you comfortable with comfortable hotels and some planned activities?\n*   **Luxury:** Are you seeking high-end accommodations, private tours, and exclusive experiences?\n\n**3. Where are you arriving from (your nearest airport/train station)?** This will help determine travel time and feasibility.\n\n**4. Time of Year:**  The season greatly impacts which destinations are ideal.\n    *   **Summer (April-June):**  Hill stations are best to escape the heat.\n    *   **Monsoon (July-September):**  Some areas are prone to landslides; check weather conditions.\n    *   **Autumn (October-November):** Pleasant weather, good for sightseeing.\n    *   **Winter (December-March):**  Cold in the mountains, but good for visiting historical cities.\n\n**In the meantime, here are a few possible itineraries based on common interests:**\n\n**Option 1:  Hill Station Escape (Mountains & Nature - Good for Summer)**\n\n*   **Destination:**  Shimla or Manali (Himachal Pradesh)\n*   **Day 1:** Arrive in Delhi, take an overnight bus/train to Shimla/Manali.\n*   **Day 2:** Explore Shimla/Manali: Visit Jakhoo Temple (Shimla), Hadimba Temple (Manali), Mall Road, enjoy scenic views.\n*   **Day 3:** Day trip to Kufri (near Shimla) for adventure activities or Solang Valley (near Manali) for paragliding/zorbing (seasonal).\n*   **Day 4:** Travel back to Delhi by bus/train.\n\n**Option 2:  Historical Triangle (History & Culture - Good for Autumn/Winter)**\n\n*   **Destination:** Agra & Fatehpur Sikri\n*   **Day 1:** Arrive in Delhi, take a train/bus to Agra (approx. 2-3 hours). Visit the Agra Fort.\n*   **Day 2:** Visit the Taj Mahal (sunrise is highly recommended!), explore Mehtab Bagh (for Taj view).\n*   **Day 3:** Day trip to Fatehpur Sikri (a UNESCO World Heritage Site), return to Agra.\n*   **Day 4:** Travel back to Delhi by train/bus.  Consider adding a half-day in Delhi to see India Gate or Humayun's Tomb before departing.\n\n**Option 3:  Spiritual & Serene (Relaxation & Spirituality - Good year-round, but check weather)**\n\n*   **Destination:**  Rishikesh (Uttarakhand)\n*   **Day 1:** Arrive in Delhi, take a bus/train to Rishikesh (approx. 6-7 hours).\n*   **Day 2:** Explore Rishikesh: Visit Lakshman Jhula, Ram Jhula, attend the Ganga Aarti at Triveni Ghat.\n*   **Day 3:** Yoga/meditation session, river rafting (depending on season), explore local markets.\n*   **Day 4:** Travel back to Delhi.\n\n**Option 4: Amritsar (Food, Culture & History - Good Year Round)**\n*   **Destination:** Amritsar\n*   **Day 1:** Arrive in Amritsar. Check in to your hotel. Take a tour of the Golden Temple.\n*   **Day 2:** Visit the Partition Museum and Wagah Border\n*   **Day 3:** Try local foods. Visit the markets.\n*   **Day 4:** Visit Gobindgarh Fort. Depart.\n\n**To help me tailor the perfect recommendation for you, please tell me more about your preferences!**\n",
